<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">The exp penalty is because we are a good melee class that can also cast spells. Being able to cast spells adds a lot of versatility to a class. For example: We couldn't fear kite without spells therefore we couldn't solo effectively. We can make ourselve invisible vs undead and in general with spells. We couldn't HEAL ourselves without spells and our downtime rival that of warriors...etc<br>
Being able to cast opens up a lot of options and makes playing more interesting as it enables you to do things in more ways. Most melee classes give up casting for the tradeoff of being great at their melee roles. SK's are basically a warrior that does less damage but makes up for less melee damage in magical damage (DoT's and such) and other magical abilities (above listed). It is a great advantage for any melee class to be able to cast spells as it gives so many more options.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
