<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Actually, this is a good question.<br>
As far as memory serves, the original idea was that Shadowknights were the most powerful class in the game. Eventually that was lost somewhere in the “game balancing” scheme.<br>
So here we are, the “most powerful” class in the game, that no longer is most powerful, but with the obscene experience penalty that was originally associated with this class.<br>
Yes, SK’s pay the highest experience penalty in the game. I play a human Sk (actually, I haven’t played the game in over 2 weeks now, all the di*ks with as*hole attitude really pis*sed me off). Humans do not pay race penalty (correct me if I’m wrong), only class penalty.<br>
Choosing human made leveling somewhat easier. At the same time I’m kicking myself now for not choosing a Troll. Even though Troll Sk’s pay the highest experience/race penalty they are the most fearsome and powerful of all SK’s. I have met a few who leveled faster that I have with my human SK.<br>
Trolls hit way harder and can get their stats (even Intelligence) way higher than a human.<br>
I played with a troll SK, both of us same level,  and he tore through mobs that I wouldn’t even consider tackling.<br>
Anyway, going back to the subject, I don’t care what someone says, Paladins, Rouges, and even Rangers can whoop our butts (Rangers not always, but still…).Before some of you start boasting “Not my as*!, you stupid pri*k”, YES YOUR  AS* TOO! I have played quite a bit, but I still find my pet to be just a long lasting, low level DOT (decent for hunting alone, useless for dueling). HT hits for far less that it should (I get giddy like a little school girl when the mob doesn’t resist more than 50% of HT). <br>
During my last game in Overthere, I found that blue mobs tend to resist 60 – 80% of my spells (that’s 6 to 8 out of 10). So this is what makes us powerful, right? Is this the reason for the experience penalty? <br>
The experience penalty is a joke. It should be the same as that for Paladins. Both classes are just about the same in a fight. Both have spells to counteract each other. Both can hit as hard. A paladin will shake off an HT and give himself a LOH. All of the sudden you have to kill the bugger all over again. We can darkness, they can blind, and so on. The list goes forever. <br>
SK’s pay for being “evil” (From personal experience most SK’s play like they would Paladins though. All cool, nice and honorable. And most Paladins are complete pri*ks) in not being very liked in most zones. Many times I found myself being chased after by some stupid low level NPC who decided to be brave and attacked me for no reason.  <br>
Since I preferred to have at least dubious standing with most NPC’s, killing that dumb as* NPC was not an option. Call me sentimental but I like hanging out in the cities. <br>
I know this is a game (I’m not that far gone into madness. I still can distinguish make believe from real, I think… HEHE), but how the hell does a NPC know what god my character worships and what class he/she is? Can you do that in RL? Can you go up to someone and right away pick out if  the person standing next to you is a store clerk or a professional assassin? Or how about their religion (Harry Crishnas, or whatever they call them selves, are an exception to the rule…)?<br>
There I go again ranting off the subject. Back to the EXP penalty issue.<br>
When the game first came out there was a reason for this experience penalty. Now since all the “balancing” there is no real reason for it. But as they say “it’s as it should be, live with it”.<p>

<br>
Enough of my bad attitude for one day. Have fun and don’t forget it’s only a game.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
