<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I don't have the exact details about the experience distribution chart but here it goes:<br>
Everyone in a group gains experience at the same rate. A hybrid or a non human will absorb more of the overall experience for each kill in order to be "experience even" with the rest of the group.<br>
This is not just a SK issue, any hybrid/non human pays some kind of experience penalty.<br>
A group composed of non hybrid classes will level faster than one made out of hybrid/non hybrid player mix. <br>
For example: a group composed of a cleric, a warrior and a wizard will most likely level faster than one composed of a SK, a ranger, a shaman and a paladin since the hybrids are eating at each other's experience. <p>

I hope this explanation helps.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
