<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I though about it and came up with a clearer explanation.<br>
Experience is divided equally among all players in a group so they are experience even.<br>
Game takes into account the level, class and race of each party member when distributing the experience.<br>
As a rule, a warrior requires less experience than a SK to get to the same level.<br>
I’ll use this as an example (I know this is off, I'm just using it as an example): <br>
for a warrior it will take a certain amount of exp to fill up an experience bubble. It will take SK the same experience just to fill up half a bubble. <br>
Even though all the experience is divided equally among all players in the group the warrior will still level faster than the SK since it takes less experience for him to gain a level than it does the SK. <br>
The warrior and everyone else in the group suffers from the SK’s experience penalty. They could be leveling faster without him/her in their group. But now they all pay a penalty to be experience even.<br>
This is not SK only issue. Non humans and hybrid classes pay some kind of penalty, but SK's pay the highest of it all.<br>
Add to this a race like troll and you have the most penalized combo in the game. <br>
Well, this is how I understand it.<hr>--- END OF LINE ---</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
