<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">A lot of this information came from the program that Verant was trying desperately to ban.  If anyone has ever used it, you would know what monsters were in zone, what level, how many hitpoints and experience points it is worth. (Btw, it shows information on people too, so all you people /anon aren't safe either.)  Doing simple math, people were able to extrapolate the data and make charts showing what Verant didn't want us to see.<p>

For example:<br>
You have a human warrior,  troll sk and high-elf cleric in group.<br>
The warrior's take on exp earned would be something like this (warrior/warrior+cleric+sk)*xp.  An easy way to see this is to put numbers here.<br>
The human warrior numbers would be 100 (for race) x 9 (warrior class) = 900<br>
The troll sk numbers would be 120 (for race) x 14 (sk class) = 1680<br>
The high elf cleric numbers would be 100 (for race) x 10 (cleric class) = 1000<p>

The sk would get roughly 46.9% of the xp earned in that group, the warrior would get 25.1% and the cleric 27.9%.<p>

I'm simplifying this information, I believe there is more here, such as levels which I'm not taking into account.  But I'm sure you see what's going on and now understand why some people are not happy with hybrids in their groups.  <p>

Just imagine if it was just warrior, warrior and cleric for the group, the warrior would be getting 32.1% and the cleric the other 35.7%.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
