<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I think its a lot easier to find out how exp works. I dont know this, its just my opinion on how things work. In a group everyone gets the same amount of exp (if all levels are equal). But as someone allready said, a shadowknight needs a lot more exp to fill up a bubble of exp than f.i. a warrior or a druid. I have two rather high-level characters, being a druid and a shadowknight and what i see is that when i die, i seem to loose a lot exp on my SK. Now that makes me think that i loose as much exp as on my druid at the same level, but since one bub of exp for my SK is a LOT more exp than one bub of exp for my druid, it just looks like im loosing less on my SK. So in groups it really doesnt matter if u have a lot of hybrids or non-hybrids in there... i know that as a fact too since i play a lot with my girlfriend. She gets the same amount of exp if she groups with my SK or my druid. I hope this clears some things up<p>

